Sensitivity Analysis

Pietryka

April 4, 2017

This document implements sensitivity analysis Described by VanderWeele, Tyler J. 2011. Sensitivity Analysis for Contagion Effects in Social Networks. Sociological Methods & Research 40(2): 240-55.
http://smr.sagepub.com/content/40/2/240.short

Sensitivity analysis for binary DV

First column of Table 1, p 247:

r code:

#the estimated effect, expressed as odds ratio
odds.ratio <- 1.57

#the odds ratio of the effect of unmeasured factor on Y
gamma <- c(1.2, 1.5, 1.8, 2, 2.5, 3, 4)

#prevelence of u (latent unmeasured factor) in treatment, expressed as proportion
pi.1 <- .6

#prevelence of u (latent unmeasured factor) in control, expressed as proportion
pi.0 <- .4

#the bias
bias.6.4 <- (1 + (gamma - 1) * pi.1) / (1 + (gamma - 1) * pi.0)

#the estimate corrected for assumed level of bias
corrected <-  odds.ratio / bias.6.4
round(corrected, 2)
## [1] 1.51 1.45 1.40 1.37 1.32 1.28 1.23

Sensitivity analysis for continous DV

Page 251, paragraph 2:

r code:

#the estimated effect, expressed as beta coefficient
effect <- 0.29

#effect of U (latent unmeasured factor) on Y , expressed as beta coefficient
gamma <-  .87

#prevelence diffrence in U (latent unmeasured factor) b/w treatment and control
delta <- .33

#the bias
bias.87.33 <- delta * gamma

#the estimate corrected for assumed level of bias
corrected <- effect - bias.87.33
corrected
## [1] 0.0029
